**Investigated**: The primary session validated Story 7.3 implementation through comprehensive DoD checks including test execution (376 server + client tests passing), TypeScript compilation (zero errors), and linting (0 errors). The session explored the complete audio system architecture including the Pinia audio store (267 lines), Web Audio API engine with three GainNode channels, 24 placeholder sound files (448KB total), integration points across GameTable.vue, TileRackItem.vue, useRoomConnection.ts, reactions store, AudioSettingsPanel UI component, and comprehensive test coverage (53 audio-related tests). The validation confirmed all 8 acceptance criteria were satisfied with evidence.

**Learned**: The audio system uses a clean architectural pattern: Web Audio API directly (no external libraries) with lazy AudioContext initialization, three independent GainNode chains for gameplay/notification/ambient channels, and module-scope engine state to avoid Vue reactivity overhead. Sound triggering follows separation of concerns: game events via resolvedAction watcher in GameTable.vue, UI interactions via component event handlers (drag sounds), and victory celebration through event-based @motifPlay emission. The timer-warning sound exists in the type system and has audio files but remains unwired - TURN_TIMER_NUDGE fires turn-ping instead, with timer-warning available for future countdown UI features. LocalStorage persistence follows the handGuidancePreferences.ts pattern (manual JSON serialization) maintaining consistency with existing stores. Test architecture mocks Web Audio API and audio store cleanly to prevent browser API calls in happy-dom environment.

